#!/bin/bash
if ! [[ -d env ]];then echo "virtualenv directory \"env\" does not exist! Please create by running: virtualenv env" exit 1 fi
if ! [[ -f requirements.txt ]];then echo "requirements.txt file does not exist! Please create by running pip3 freeze > requirements.txt" exit 1 fi
if ! command -v waitress-serve &>/dev/null;then echo "waitress-serve is not installed! Install by running pip3 install waitress" exit 1 fi
my_ip=$(curl -s icanhazip.com)
echo "************************************************************************************" echo "You can now test the application by browsing to this URL: http://${my_ip}:8080/yossi" echo "************************************************************************************"
waitress-serve application:application
